The paper deals with the complexity of distributed computing in the LOCAL model, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The focus is on the bipartite maximal matching problem, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses lower bounds, which is a topic in Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The use of automatic round elimination techniques is related to Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Information Theory (cs.IT).
